sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Schedule Task Creation From Env Variable Or Potentially Suspicious Path Via Schtasks.EXE
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects Schtask creations that point to a suspicious folder or an environment variable often used by malware

match_context.values: @{Product=Microsoft\xae Windows\xae Operating System; CurrentDirectory=C:\Users\Bruno\Desktop\; OriginalFileName=schtasks.exe; Hashes=SHA1=3A8EFD34E448B6E8905DDFF2B49816C233927ACD,MD5=F8564018F0382D7F6EC0515D38AD7966,SHA256=F0024EB58326ECAE6437237C3125CE75BE6C621EA4B1303FD5B9DFE96B1DFF32,IMPHASH=96F93525922FF1BB66DEE7D1A85E7A11; Description=Task Scheduler Configuration Tool; FileVersion=10.0.22621.1 (WinBuild.160101.0800); ParentCommandLine="C:\Windows\System32\cmd.exe" /c schtasks /create /f /sc onlogon /rl highest /tn "Notepad++" /tr '"C:\Users\Bruno\AppData\Roaming\Notepad++.exe"' & exit; CommandLine=schtasks  /create /f /sc onlogon /rl highest /tn "Notepad++" /tr '"C:\Users\Bruno\AppData\Roaming\Notepad++.exe"' ; EventID=1; ParentImage=C:\Windows\SysWOW64\cmd.exe; IntegrityLevel=High; Image=C:\Windows\SysWOW64\schtasks.exe; Company=Microsoft Corporation}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Read Contents From Stdin Via Cmd.EXE
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detect the use of "<" to read and potentially execute a file via cmd.exe

match_context.values: @{CommandLine=C:\Windows\System32\cmd.exe /c schtasks /create /f /sc onlogon /rl highest /tn Notepad++ /tr "C:\\Users\\<USER>\\AppData\\Roaming\\Notepad++.exe" & exit; Image=C:\Windows\System32\cmd.exe; EventID=1}
